---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Testimonials & Social Proof for Chiropractors | SocialProof" description="New patients research before booking. Collect patient testimonials and display them on your chiropractic website. Free to start. No code required." canonical="https://socialproof.dev/for/chiropractors">
<style>
    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; margin: 0; background: #fff; color: #111; }
    nav { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: 1rem 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; }
    nav a.logo { font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #111; text-decoration: none; }
    nav .nav-links a { margin-left: 1.5rem; color: #555; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    nav .cta-nav { background: #111; color: #fff !important; padding: 0.45rem 1rem; border-radius: 6px; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .for-badge { display: inline-block; background: #f0fdf4; color: #16a34a; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: .35rem .75rem; border-radius: 99px; margin-bottom: 1rem; border: 1px solid #bbf7d0; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
    .hero h1 span { color: #4f46e5; }
    .hero p { font-size: 1.15rem; color: #444; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; }
    .hero-cta { display: inline-block; background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; padding: .85rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 1rem; }
    .hero-cta:hover { background: #3730a3; }
    section { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 2rem; }
    h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .pain-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 1.25rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .pain-card { background: #f9f9f9; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.25rem; }
    .pain-card .icon { font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: .5rem; }
    .pain-card h3 { margin: 0 0 .5rem; font-size: 0.97rem; font-weight: 700; }
    .pain-card p { margin: 0; color: #555; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.6; }
    .steps { counter-reset: step; list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .steps li { counter-increment: step; display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .steps li::before { content: counter(step); min-width: 2rem; height: 2rem; background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.9rem; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
    .steps li .step-text h3 { margin: 0 0 .25rem; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; }
    .steps li .step-text p { margin: 0; color: #555; font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.6; }
    .testimonial-example { background: #f8f7ff; border-left: 4px solid #4f46e5; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 0 10px 10px 0; margin: 2rem 0; font-size: 1rem; color: #333; line-height: 1.7; font-style: italic; }
    .testimonial-example cite { display: block; margin-top: .75rem; font-style: normal; font-size: 0.88rem; color: #888; }
    .skeptic-box { background: #fff5f5; border: 1.5px solid #fecaca; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .skeptic-box h3 { margin: 0 0 .75rem; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; color: #991b1b; }
    .skeptic-box p { margin: 0; color: #555; font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; }
    .prompt-list { background: #f0fdf4; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .prompt-list h3 { margin: 0 0 .75rem; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; color: #166534; }
    .prompt-list ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; color: #555; font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 2; }
    .cta-section { background: #111; color: #fff; text-align: center; padding: 4rem 2rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
    .cta-section h2 { color: #fff; }
    .cta-section p { color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .cta-section a { background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; padding: .85rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 1rem; }
    footer { text-align: center; padding: 2rem; color: #888; font-size: 0.85rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; }
    footer a { color: #888; text-decoration: none; margin: 0 .75rem; }
</style>

<nav>
  <a href="/" class="logo">SocialProof</a>
  <div class="nav-links">
    <a href="/for/">Who it's for</a>
    <a href="/#pricing">Pricing</a>
    <a href="/app/signup" class="cta-nav">Try free</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<div class="hero">
  <div class="for-badge">🦴 For Chiropractors</div>
  <h1>New patients are<br/><span>skeptical by default.</span><br/>Testimonials change that.</h1>
  <p>Chiropractic care is a considered decision — people research, doubt, and compare before booking. Patient testimonials on your website answer the questions they're too nervous to ask out loud.</p>
  <a href="/app/signup" class="hero-cta">Start collecting testimonials free</a>
</div>

<section>
  <h2>The skeptic's journey to your door</h2>
  <div class="skeptic-box">
    <h3>What your next patient is thinking before they call</h3>
    <p>"Does chiropractic actually work? Will it make things worse? Is this doctor legit? What if it's a scam? My friend said it helped their back but I'm not sure…" — Every credential you list is filtered through this lens of doubt. The one thing that cuts through it: a real person saying "here's what happened to me."</p>
  </div>

  <h2>What holds chiropractors back from great testimonials</h2>
  <div class="pain-grid">
    <div class="pain-card">
      <div class="icon">🔒</div>
      <h3>HIPAA awareness (real or imagined)</h3>
      <p>You're cautious about patient information. SocialProof testimonials are 100% patient-initiated — they choose to share, which is completely compliant.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pain-card">
      <div class="icon">😶</div>
      <h3>Patients feel awkward writing reviews</h3>
      <p>A blank form is intimidating. When you send a direct link with a short prompt, patients follow through at much higher rates.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pain-card">
      <div class="icon">⭐</div>
      <h3>Reviews go to Google, not your site</h3>
      <p>Google reviews are great for search. But they don't live on the page where a skeptical visitor is deciding whether to book.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pain-card">
      <div class="icon">💻</div>
      <h3>Tech feels like a project</h3>
      <p>You run a healthcare practice, not a software company. SocialProof takes 5 minutes to set up — no IT, no code.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section style="background:#f9f9f9; padding: 3rem 2rem;">
  <div style="max-width:900px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h2>How to use SocialProof in your chiropractic practice</h2>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>
        <div class="step-text">
          <h3>Sign up for free in 2 minutes</h3>
          <p>You get a unique collection link immediately. No developer, no credit card.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="step-text">
          <h3>Send the link after a patient has results</h3>
          <p>Text it after 3-4 visits when they're already feeling better. Email it in your post-appointment follow-up. The timing makes all the difference.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="step-text">
          <h3>Approve testimonials before they go live</h3>
          <p>You control everything. Nothing appears on your website until you approve it. Pick the most specific, credible patient stories.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="step-text">
          <h3>Embed on your practice website with one click</h3>
          <p>Copy-paste a single snippet. Works on any website — WordPress, Squarespace, Wix, custom HTML, or your practice management system's site.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <div class="testimonial-example">
      "I'd been dealing with lower back pain for two years. I was skeptical about chiropractic — I thought it was a bit of a scam, honestly. After 6 sessions with Dr. Patel I'm completely pain free for the first time since my injury. I wish I'd come sooner."
      <cite>— David R., patient</cite>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Great prompts to get specific testimonials</h2>
  <div class="prompt-list">
    <h3>💬 Ask patients these questions when requesting a testimonial</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>"What were you dealing with before you came in, and what's different now?"</li>
      <li>"Were you skeptical about chiropractic care before trying it?"</li>
      <li>"How many sessions did it take before you felt a difference?"</li>
      <li>"What would you tell a friend who's thinking about chiropractic but isn't sure?"</li>
      <li>"Is there anything about the experience that surprised you?"</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <p style="color:#555; font-size:0.92rem; line-height:1.7;">Specific answers convert skeptical visitors. "My back pain is gone" is vague. "I had a disc bulge at L4-L5 and after 8 weeks I'm back to running 5 miles" is specific and credible.</p>
</section>

<div class="cta-section">
  <h2>Turn patient results into new patient bookings.</h2>
  <p>Free forever for 1 widget. No code. Works with any practice website.</p>
  <a href="/app/signup">Try SocialProof free →</a>
</div>

<footer>
  <a href="/">SocialProof</a>
  <a href="/for/">Who it's for</a>
  <a href="/#pricing">Pricing</a>
  <a href="/app/signup">Sign up free</a>
</footer>
</Base>
